Student Advisor Bot Using Amazon Lex
Objective
Build a simple chatbot named "Student Advisor Bot" with two intents: AskAboutAssignments and GetCourseInformation, using Amazon Lex and AWS Lambda for fulfillment.
1. Create the Bot in Amazon Lex
•	Bot Name: StudentAdvisorBot
•	Language: English
•	Session Timeout: 5 minutes
•	Intents:
1.	AskAboutAssignments
	Sample utterances:
	“What assignments do I have?”
	“Do I have any assignments due?”
	“List my upcoming assignments”
2.	GetCourseInformation
	Sample utterances:
	“Tell me about {Course Name}”
	“What is {Course Name} about?”
	“Course details for {Course Name}”

2.	Fulfillment Lambda Function
•	Function Name: StudentAdvisorBot
•	Runtime: Python 3.12
•	Lambda Code:


import json
def lambda_handler(event, context):
    intent_name = event["sessionState"]["intent"]["name"]

    if intent_name == "AskAboutAssignments":
        return respond("You currently have 2 assignments due: Essay 1 (due Sept 20) and Lab 3 (due Sept 25).")

    elif intent_name == "GetCourseInformation":
        slots = event["sessionState"]["intent"].get("slots", {})
        course = slots.get("CourseName", {}).get("value", {}).get("interpretedValue", "your course")
        return respond(f"{course} is an introductory course covering key concepts and best practices.")

    else:
        return respond("Sorry, I don’t know how to handle that yet.")

def respond(message):
    return {
        "sessionState": {
            "dialogAction": {"type": "Close"},
            "intent": {
                "name": "StudentAdvisorBot",
                "state": "Fulfilled"
            }
        },
        "messages": [
            {"contentType": "PlainText", "content": message}
        ]
    }
